  <brief_title>Prophylactic Post-Cesarean Incisional Negative-pressure Wound Therapy in Morbidly Obese Patients</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Albany Medical College</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Albany Medical College</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To evaluate the effectiveness of negative-pressure wound therapy in decreasing wound
      complications in morbidly obese patients (BMI greater than of equal to 40) at Albany Medical
      Center Hospital. Retrospective data will be collected regarding morbidly obese patients who
      have undergone cesarean section and patients will be recruited to have the intervention
      (negative-pressure wound therapy) applied and outcomes will be evaluated.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
